On Holocaust Remembrance Day, the President pays tribute to the six million Jews and other victims of Nazi brutality who were killed during the Holocaust. He emphasizes the importance of never forgetting and ensuring that such atrocities never happen again. He also draws strength from the survivors, liberators, and righteous individuals who stood against the Holocaust. The President calls for a united front against anti-Semitism, bigotry, and hatred, with the goal of creating a more just, free, and secure world for future generations.